# PageIndex Website Experiment — environment template
#
# SETUP:  cp .env.example .env   then fill in the key(s) you need.
# The real .env is gitignored — never commit it.
#
# WHY THIS LEVEL: PageIndex loads env vars via python-dotenv. We always run it
# from vendor/PageIndex/, and load_dotenv() walks up the directory tree, so a
# .env at this repo root is found automatically. Keeping it here (rather than
# inside the vendored vendor/PageIndex/ submodule) means the credential belongs
# to the experiment, not the tool, and lives next to this template.
#
# WHICH KEYS YOU NEED depend on the experiment condition:
#   IDX-D   (deterministic index)       -> NONE (built from Markdown headings; no LLM)
#   IDX-C   (cloud index + summaries)   -> OPENAI_API_KEY (or another LiteLLM provider)
#   RET-OAI (OpenAI retriever/agent)    -> OPENAI_API_KEY
#   RET-ANT (Claude retriever/agent)    -> ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
#   IDX-O / RET-OLL (Ollama, local)     -> NONE (needs a running Ollama service instead)
#
# Multi-provider routing is via LiteLLM: https://docs.litellm.ai/docs/providers

OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-your-openai-key-here
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-your-anthropic-key-here
